James de Villiers, News24Sicelo Goodwill Xulu. (Photo: Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; The managing director of Johannesburg&rsquo;s power utility City Power has been relieved from all his contractual responsibilities, City of Johannesburg mayor Herman Mashaba said on Monday.&nbsp;In a statement, Mashaba said a forensic report tabled in front of City Power&rsquo;s board last week detailed serious misconduct by managing director Sicelo Xulu.&nbsp;Xulu was placed on special leave in February.&nbsp;The Board would ordinarily institute a disciplinary hearing, however Xulu&rsquo;s contract will expire in August and as such the city would not be able to complete a disciplinary hearing, Mashaba said.&nbsp;Xulu was hence released from all his contractual agreements.&nbsp;&ldquo;This decision &ndash; which I fully support &ndash; will begin the process of restoring good governance and ending corruption at the power utility,&rdquo; Mashaba said.&nbsp;&ldquo;Weak corporate governance and corruption at City Power have for too long been allowed to rob our residents of much needed service delivery.&rdquo;Mashaba said he has instructed the city&rsquo;s forensic and investigation unit to keep all relevant information for possible future criminal charges against city officials implicated.&nbsp;He said weak governance has been made evident by alleged corruption and gross mismanagement of the Eldorado Park and Hopefield substation contracts.&ldquo;Millions of Rands were paid to a contractor who has not performed the work required,&rdquo; Mashaba said.&nbsp;&ldquo;Had City Power&rsquo;s governance and management systems not been eroded by corruption, quality services would have been delivered to the residents of these communities.&rdquo; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.